{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"51":"The Book of Drinks"},"section_detail":{"51":{"hadithnumber_first":5540,"hadithnumber_last":5758,"arabicnumber_first":5540,"arabicnumber_last":5758}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":5617,"arabicnumber":5617,"text":"Rapporté par Ibn 'Umar : Le Messager d'Allah ﷺ a interdit Al-Hantam. J'ai demandé : « Qu'est-ce que Al-Hantam ? » Il a répondu : « La jarre en terre cuite. »","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim"}],"reference":{"book":51,"hadith":79}}]}